            <title>[KAFKA-4925] Add a configurable delay to the initial consumer group rebalance</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4925</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As per &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-134%3A+Delay+initial+consumer+group+rebalance&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/KAFKA/KIP-134%3A+Delay+initial+consumer+group+rebalance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add a broker side config that will enable the GroupCoordinator to delay the initial rebalance for a new/empty consumer group&lt;/p&gt;</description>
